Pin should have cross reference id set up in CFM DB *SELECT* * *FROM* CF.CMRCL_CUST_ID_XREF *WHERE* CMRCL_CUST_ID = '100818' or [https://dv-api.autozone.com/customers/commercial/v3/customers/100818/cross-references?referenceTypeCode=MONRO&isActiveFl=true]

Segmentation - Trickle Invoices - Should be Yes

*Test Scenarios:*
Regular Non VDP order with PO required pin as [z] format
Split order with PO required pin as[zzz-abc] format

Need to cover some negative scenarios:
Validate the pin without cross reference id , pin which is not in customer group but has cross reference and pin which is both not in customer group and not having cross reference id.

We need to follow the below steps:

1) Create an azeo order and Generate invoice

2) Validate in trickle that invoice has been sent to atg [trickles@qa-tracker-xl01|mailto:trickles@qa-tracker-xl01] CommInvoiceLoad.log

3) Validate in atg that invoice info was received [ua000281@dv-blazer1-xl62|mailto:ua000281@dv-blazer1-xl62] [ua000281@dv-blazer1-xl62|mailto:ua000281@dv-blazer1-xl62]
in the path /az/srvr/atg/invoice reports/pending_invoice

4) Execute method [http://dv-blazer1-xl62.autozone.com:8280/dyn/admin/nucleus/autozone/pro/integrations/invoicereport/InvoiceReportService/?shouldInvokeMethod=processInvoicedReports] in dyn/admin

5) Validate Generated ASN file in /az/srvr/atg/pending_asn

CC: [~30081459]

*Test Scenarios:*

Validate that ASN Json is generated when sending AZEO order with Monroe EDI configured pin and with po sent in request (Single Non VDP, Split Order) - Invoice through picking app
Validate that ASN Json is generated when sending AZEO order with Monroe EDI configured pin and with po not sent in request (Multi Non VDPs, Multi VDPs) - Invoice through order validation/gemini

        submit order with pin which has no cross reference id
        submit order with pin which has cross reference but the pin is not MONROE EDI ORDER FEED
        submit order with pin which is not MONROE EDI ORDER FEED and also not having cross reference id

Validate the ASN Json is generated when sending AZEO order with different source id and Monroe configured pin

When pin is not monroe configured
When pin does not have reference id in CF DB

[~30081459] in regards of "When pin does not have reference id in CF DB" that is not a valid scenario. When we process the 810 files in monro edi processor job if the input data has an invalid cross reference the order will not be generated.

That means that orders are created only for pins having a cross reference, and therefore when the order is invoiced and the ASN is generated the pin will have always a crossreference id.

cc [~10877817]

Validated below scenarios in QA and works fine through AZEO service. Batch process will be handled in EOTP-1802.
 
1. Validate that ASN Json is generated when sending AZEO order with Monroe EDI configured pin and with po sent in request (Single Non VDP, Split Order) - Invoice through picking app
2. Validate that ASN Json is generated when sending AZEO order with Monroe EDI configured pin and with po not sent in request (Multi Non VDPs, Multi VDPs) - Invoice through order validation/gemini
3. Validate the ASN Json is generated when sending AZEO order with different source id and Monroe configured pin

[^EOTP-1794.docx] 

Below scenario is not valid when we create order directly through AZEO endpoint. Only the batch process will check for cross reference id and whether the pin is in monroe configured or not. [~10568198] Could you please confirm on this understanding.

Validate that ASN Json is not generated when pin is not configured or cross reference id is not available the pin 
        submit order with pin which has no cross reference id
        submit order with pin which has cross reference but the pin is not MONROE EDI ORDER FEED
        submit order with pin which is not MONROE EDI ORDER FEED and also not having cross reference id

Note: The batch process for above scenarios will be validated in EOTP-1802

[~30081459] 

When pin is not in MONRO group then the invoice info won't be sent to AZPRO to generate the ASN.

Any pin that is not in Invoice Recon or (MONRO, MAVIS) group id we be sent to ATG by default to be processed as AZPRO or Punchout order. If the Order was created in AZEO then the info will be rejected in AZPRO (that is expected).

!https://b2b-devops-docs.apps.prod.mem.cloud.autozone.com/assets/images/Trickle/trickleInvoice.png!

Only when the order was created by a PIN in MONTO group will generate the ASN file

Validated in stage. Working as expected
